COPS are looking for a man who allegedly stabbed and killed his ex-girlfriend in Tembisa, Ekurhuleni, on Monday, 30 January. It’s reported that the 29-year-old woman was with her two children waiting for their scholar transport when the ex-boyfriend arrived and allegedly stabbed her in the upper body with a sharp object. Gauteng police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Mavela Masondo said the victim was certified dead on the scene. “The motive for the killing cannot be confirmed at this stage. Police are looking for the suspect,” said Masondo. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments Anyone who has information that might help put the perpetrator behind bars is advised to alert the police immediately. 15:34 On Monday afternoon, the 27-year-old man was arrested for murder of a 29-year-old
woman at Mayibuye on Monday morning, 30 January. The suspect was brought to Tembisa South Police Station by
his family. He has was then taken by Rabie Ridge Detectives. 